Install Base Targeting: The Hidden Goldmine
One of the fastest-growing demand generation strategies in 2026 is install base targeting — identifying companies that currently use a competing or complementary technology and reaching them with a displacement or integration message.

AI makes install base data actionable at scale. Natural language processing tools can now crawl job postings, LinkedIn profiles, technology review sites, and company press releases to build a real-time picture of what technology stack a target account is running. This is then layered with intent signals to identify which of those companies are actively evaluating alternatives.

For a U.S.-based B2B technology company, this means you can build a highly targeted campaign aimed specifically at companies using a competitor's product who are also currently showing research intent around your category. This is the highest-probability outreach scenario in modern B2B selling.

